text.section:
To qualify for a license to practice as a radiologist assistant, an applicant shall:
Be issued a general license to perform medical radiation technology;
Complete an advanced academic program with a nationally recognized radiology curriculum that results in a baccalaureate degree, post baccalaureate certificate, or graduate degree and incorporates a radiologist-directed clinical preceptorship;
Be certified in advanced cardiac life support; and
Be certified as a radiologist assistant by the American Registry of Radiologic Technologists.
